    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName ref="#people/124"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Fridericus</persName> divina favente gratia
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex augustus</rs>. Potestatis nostre nos
                        ortatur auctoritas universis ecclesiis per Romanum imperium constitutis
                        regia in omnibus provisione consulere earumque possessiones a nostris
                        predecessoribus pia devotione eis collatas confirmationis nostre privilegio
                        roborare. Eapropter omnibus ecclesie dei fidelibus tam futuris quam
                        presentibus volumus esse cognitum, quod nos interventu karissimi nostri
                            <persName ref="#people/525" key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops">Arnoldi
                            Coloniensis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> Italici regni <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">abbatiam</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/53"
                            key="#Houses #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Castle #Comitatus #Public_exactions #Tolls #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Churches/religious_bodies #Monasteries"
                            >sancti Sisti</orgName> infra <rs key="#Walls">muros</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/43" key="#Walls">Placencie</placeName> constitutam
                        ab <persName ref="#people/55" key="#Queen">Engilberga</persName> quondam <rs
                            key="#Queen">imperatrice</rs> constructam, que eciam ad ius et
                        proprietatem regni nostri pertinere dignoscitur, in <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">regiam protectionem</rs> suscipimus et
                        presentis scripti privilegio communimus confirmantes ei omnia iura omnesque
                        possessiones a nostris predecessoribus regibus seu imperatoribus, reginis
                        aut imperatricibus sive aliorum bonorum hominum largitione concessas. <rs
                            key="#Royal_slave">Familias quoque utriusque sexus</rs> cum <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtibus</rs> et <rs key="#Churches/religious_bodies"
                            >capellis</rs> earumque appendiciis cum omnibus <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castellis</rs>, <rs key="#Houses">casis</rs>, <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals">campis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder"
                            >pascuis, pratis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, salectis, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs>, aquis aquarumque
                        decursibus, <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscationibus</rs>, omnem <rs key="#Public_exactions">redditionem</rs>
                        et <rs key="#Districtio">districtionem</rs> per singula loca et <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitatus</rs> de omnibus rebus et possessionibus
                        eiusdem monasterii, que ad partes publicas pertinere videntur, et cum
                        omnibus rebus ad predictum monasterium iuste et legaliter respicientibus in
                        integrum confirmamus et corroboramus, ex quibus hec propriis duximus
                        exprimenda vocabulis, scilicet <placeName ref="#places/14"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><geogName ref="#estates/76"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >caput Tribium</geogName></placeName>, <geogName ref="#estates/1518"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/1921"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Cornelianum</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1538">curtem Reginam</geogName>, <placeName
                            ref="#places/1923"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><geogName ref="#estates/1520"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Octauum</geogName></placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/97"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Roncariola, que vocantur Castrum Nouum</placeName>, cum ecclesia
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1509" key="#Churches">sancti
                            Michaelis</orgName>, <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1539">Puteum Altum</geogName>, <placeName
                            ref="#places/354"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><geogName ref="#estates/112"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Sextum</geogName></placeName>, <geogName ref="#estates/1508"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/1906"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Tencariam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/1519"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/1922"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >Fontanam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#estates/1537"
                            >Scopera</geogName>,<placeName ref="#places/33"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <geogName ref="#estates/40"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Guardastallam</geogName></placeName> cum omnibus rebus, capellis et
                        universis appenditiis eius ac familiis utriusque sexus ita sane, ut
                        perhenniter in usus monachorum ibidem deo famulantium persistat, <placeName
                            ref="#places/32"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><geogName ref="#estates/38"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Luciariam</geogName></placeName> quoque et <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/1967"><geogName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/1536">Curtem Uiridem</geogName></placeName>, <geogName
                            ref="#estates/207"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/462"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Curtem Nouam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/1521"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/1924"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Riuis</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/77"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/361"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Littora Paludiana</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            ref="#estates/2007"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/2417"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Crustellum</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/80"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/362"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Villule</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/42"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/34"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Pigugaram</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/110"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/141"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >campum Miliacium</placeName></geogName> cum aliis omnibus
                        possessionibus rationabiliter adquisitis vel adquirendis. Decernimus igitur,
                        ut nullus regum seu imperatorum nec <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux nec
                            marchio</rs> nec <rs key="#Count">comes</rs> nec <rs key="#Archbishops"
                            >archiepiscopus</rs> nec <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> nec <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> nec alia quelibet ecclesiastica seu laica parva
                        magnave persona prefatum monasterium temere inquietare presumat, sed
                        presidente venerabili <persName ref="#people/1615" key="#Abbots"
                            >Berardo</persName> eiusdem cenobii tercio abbate suisque successoribus
                        maneant in perpetuum eorum, quorum collata sunt, usibus omnimodis profutura.
                        Nolumus etiam, ut ab hominibus liberis in potestate eiusdem monasterii
                        residentibus aut a familiis ipsius loci ullum <rs key="#Tolls"
                            >portonaticum</rs>, <rs key="#Teloneum">teloneum</rs> aut <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripaticum</rs> vel
                        quelibet <rs key="#Public_exactions">vectigalia</rs> aliquis requirat vel
                        exigat. Et ut hec omnia in perpetuum firma atque illibata permaneant,
                        presentem paginam sigilli nostri impressione iussimus insigniri. Testes
                        huius rei sunt: Arnoldus Coloniensis archiepiscopus, <persName
                            ref="#people/1616">Peregrinus patriarcha Aquileiensis</persName>,
                            <persName ref="#people/1617" key="#Archbishops">Hillinus</persName>
                        Treuerensis archiepiscopus, <persName ref="#people/1620" key="#Bishops"
                            >Ebrahardus Babenbergensis</persName> episcopus, <persName
                            ref="#people/1630" key="#Bishops">Ordoliebus Basiliensis
                            episcopus</persName>, Emahardus Magnopolitanus episcopus, <persName
                            ref="#people/1627" key="#Bishops">Anselmus Auelbergensis
                            episcopus</persName>, <persName ref="#people/1624" key="#Bishops"
                            >Conradus Warmatiensis episcopus</persName>, <persName
                            ref="#people/1621" key="#Marquis/duke">Henricus dux Saxonie</persName>,
                            <persName ref="#people/1623" key="#Marquis/duke">Bertoldus dux
                            Burgundie</persName>, <persName ref="#people/1625" key="#Marquis/duke"
                            >Odaccaro marchio de Stira</persName>, <persName ref="#people/1628"
                            key="#Marquis/duke">Hermannus marchio de Bade</persName>, <persName
                            ref="#people/1622" key="#Marquis/duke">Guerneherus marchio
                            Anconitanus</persName>, <persName ref="#people/1626" key="#Count"
                            >Bertoldus comes de Anedexe</persName>, <persName ref="#people/1629"
                            key="#Count">Ernestus comes de Hohenburc</persName>, <persName
                            ref="#people/1631" key="#Count">Antelmus comes de Crema</persName>,
                            <persName ref="#people/4045" key="#Count">Udalricus comes de
                            Lenzeburc</persName> et alii plurimi. Signum domni Friderici Romanorum
                        regis invictissimi. (M.) Ego Arnoldus Coloniensis archiepiscopus Italici
                        regni archicancellarius recognovi. Dat. in <placeName ref="#places/38">campo
                            Mutinensium</placeName> anno dominice incarnationis MCLV, indictione
                        IIII, regnante domno Friderico Romanorum rege glorioso, anno vero regni eius
                        IIII; feliciter amen, amen, amen. Fridericus dei gratia Romanorum rex
                        augustus.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
